<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What you need is a better haste item and/or a bigger weapon.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Any other solution to agro maintenance just doesn't allow the ego room to breath and should be shunned.<br>
<br>
mucho haste + big weapon = tons of agro.<br>
<br>
If you cannot afford better haste &amp; a big weapon?  Dont bitch about it, just accept that your gear is crap and find a solution to the problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>What about the agro is all about playskill argument?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Skill in agro management is about controlling X number of mobs and accomplishing the CC with the minimal of mana expenditure and within CC/Heal cast time constraints, in order to maintain the highest killspeed over time.<br>
<br>
If you rely on spells to establish or keep agro on the main mob then you cannot possibly ACC on the adds.  Furthermore you are delivering less dps.  Your are not pulling your weight.<br>
<br>
The main tank should at all times know what mob is hitting who and be able to decide instantly which mobs they need to agro and where to place them.<br>
<br>
If you are struggling to keep agro by chain casting, you can at best control 1 mob and any attempt to ACC will probably fail or take too long to accomplish anything.<br>
<br>
